*Vacancy: Data Engineer*
*Company: <http://Carnext.com|Carnext.com>*
*Location: Amsterdam, NL. Visa support is possible if you can reach Amsterdam.* 
Would you like to help us in building predictive models using state of the art machine learning algorithms? In solving the challenges of managing and shipping hundreds of models to production, and monitoring and tracking their performance? Would you like to build data pipelines that will generate various data sets to be used in training the models?
We are looking for a Medior/Senior Data Engineer to join our Data & Analytics team.
The team is responsible for designing, building and maintaining data solutions that are business critical for our platform. We are a fast-growing team that works on modern technology stack, including AWS Redshift, Glue and Lambda, Airflow, Terraform, Kafka 
At <http://CarNext.com|CarNext.com> you will be a technical expert with huge impact. You collaborate on a daily basis with data scientists, data engineers, software engineers and product owners to take our data platform to the next level.
You will work on various projects, such as customer demand prediction, dynamic pricing and product selection, model life cycle optimization or underlying infrastructure improvements.
*These are your challenges*
• You will expand and improve our data analytics platform
• You will develop data pipelines to and from our data warehouse to increase availability and quality of data
• You will Scale-up our cloud infrastructure (as code)
• You will Develop software for training, testing and deploying machine learning algorithms
• You will ensure the team is delivering high quality products via mentoring and education
• You will advocate software engineering best practices
*Why you will love it*
• You will be part of team and culture, that continuously grows & improve itself, colleagues, the code, and as a result, the way <http://CarNext.com|CarNext.com> delivers its product to its customers
• You will have a big impact on building a leading platform company that will disrupt the industry, using machine learning
• You will work with state of the art technologies, and you will influence the choice of new tools & technologies
• You will deal with a diverse set and growing set of data (commercial data, customer data, market data, product data )
• You go beyond prototyping and ship your code to production and have impact in 23 markets 
*You will be successful in this position if you*
• Have 4+ years of working experience in a Data Engineering role using modern technologies
• Have strong programming skills in Python, as well as database query languages (SQL)
• Have broad working experience with a modern stack in cloud services (AWS S3, EC2, Redshift, RDS, EMR, ECS)
• Have experience with data workflow management (eg: Airflow), virtualization platforms (eg: Docker), monitoring tools (eg: Grafana), version control (eg: Git)
• Have experience with data warehouse design (dimensional modelling)
• Have implemented continuous integration/ continuous delivery (CI/CD) in a production environment
• Have expertise in infrastructure as code (eg: Terraform)
• Have experience with real-time processing frameworks (eg: Kafka)
*Compensation:*
*Salary 60-80k Euro gross,* including 13th salary, 8% holiday allowance
+ benefits: excellent pension plan, bonuses.
Application on <https://corporate.carnext.com/careers/vacancies/4470797002>
If you have any questions feel free to reach me out:  <mailto:Andrey.zhelezniakov@carnext.com|Andrey.zhelezniakov@carnext.com>  
Or <https://www.linkedin.com/in/azhelezniakov/>

text:
*Vacancy: Lead Data Science*
*Company: <http://Carnext.com|Carnext.com>*
*Location: Amsterdam, NL. Visa support is possible if you can reach Amsterdam.* 
Do you have broad hands-on experience with applying regression-, (boosted) tree-, and time series-based Machine Learning in a business context? Do you have working experience recruiting, coaching and inspiring a team of junior to senior data scientists?  
 We are looking for a Lead Data Science to help us growing our ecosystem to a Machine Learning driven system that finds the best cars for our customers at the best price. You will report to the Head of Data & Analytics.
 The Data & Analytics team designs, builds and maintains data solutions that are business critical for <http://CarNext.com|CarNext.com>’s platform. For example, you will lead Machine Learning based model management for customer demand prediction, dynamic pricing, and product selection. We are a fast-growing team that works with a modern cloud stack, like AWS RedShift, EC2, Lambda, Glue, and Airflow, Kafka, DBT, and Glue, Spark and Scala, and work in a dynamic environment. Data scientists themselves work on a daily basis in multidisciplinary teams with engineers, product owners, business stakeholders, and software engineers.
 *These are your challenges*
• You are responsible for central model management (23 countries).
• You will lead and grow capabilities of the Data Scientist team (currently 8 fte) to a large team from the content Drive innovation and realization of data science technology innovations, ML developments, model management of predictive algorithms.
• You will manage data science activities.
• You will co-develop and execute roadmap for data analytics solutions.
• You will partner with cross-functional teams to lead or contribute to large scale strategic projects as well as ongoing operational activities.
• You will prioritize projects across the team and allocate resources to meet business and team goals.
*Why you will love it*
• You will be part of team and culture, that continuously grows & improve itself, colleagues, the code, and as a result, the way <http://CarNext.com|CarNext.com> delivers its product to its customers.
• You will have a big impact on building a leading platform company that will disrupt the industry, using machine learning.
• You will work with state of the art technologies, and you will influence the choice of new tools & technologies.
• You will deal with a diverse set and growing set of data (commercial data, customer data, market data, product data ).
• You go beyond prototyping and ship your code to production and have an impact in 23 markets.
 *You will be successful in this position if you*
• Have a passion for problem solving data related challenges.
• Have a strong working experience and understanding of predictive modelling of structured data, like regression and XGB statistics and machine learning.
• Have strong coaching and inspirational and challenging skills.
• Have a Masters in field where statistical understanding of data is central (e.g. Mathematics, Econometrics, Statistical physics, or equivalent).
• Have Cloud computing and platforms experience.
• Are a proven communicator with technical teams.
*Compensation:*
*Salary 80-100k Euro gross,* including 13th salary, 8% holiday allowance
+ benefits: excellent pension plan, bonuses, great car allowance ( you can take cash instead of a car), We support 30% rulings  application.
Application on <https://corporate.carnext.com/careers/vacancies/4669175002>
If you have any questions feel free to reach me out:  <mailto:andrey.zhelezniakov@carnext.com|andrey.zhelezniakov@carnext.com>  
Or <https://www.linkedin.com/in/azhelezniakov/>

text:
Привет, :ods:

Ищем в команду сильных Machine Learning Research Engineers в новый проект связанный со звуком!

Для тех, кому интересна только вилка, то вот она! и дальше можно не читать
:fork:: 150k-250k

*Требования*
:python:  Хорошо умеете в Python
:pytorch1-0: Сильные навыки имплементации, тренировки и дебага моделек на pytorch
:page_facing_up: Умение читать, понимать и воспроизводить хайповые статейки
:sound: Опыт работы со звуком: ASR, TTS, Voice Conversion и прочее

*Задачи*
:speech_balloon: Делать R&D в области генерации речи
:hammer_and_pick: Читать, понимать, воспроизводить статейки и не грустить, когда они не заводятся
:recycle: Собирать прототипы, MVP, pivot-иться ;)
:small: Ужимать модельки, оптимизировать инференс и засовывать все добро в телефоны (но это не точно)

*Накинем сверху за:*
:hirsch_index: Размер вашего Хирша и публикации на топовых ML конференциях
:first_place_medal: Финалистов ACM ICPC
:kaggle: Золотые и серебряные медальки на Kaggle
:bar_chart: Яркие (но ближе к красному) хендлы на Codeforces

*Что вы отдаете:*
:brain: Мозги, креатив и душу

*Что вы получаете:*
:+1: Участие в разработке интересного и перспективного проекта с нуля
:challenge_acepted: Сложные задачи, которые больше никто не решает в вашей *парадной* ;)
:umbrella_with_rain_drops: Офис в городе дождей. Это я про Питер, если вы еще не догадались. Однако! Я специально для вас разогнал все тучки на пару месяцев вперед.
:ramen: Бесплатные обеды, корпоративы и тд.
:beers: Посиделки в уютных Питерских барах, ведь мы с вами должны жить в любви и счастье
:desktop_computer: Мощный workstation, чтобы можно было получить золото на Kaggle за одну ночь, и никто бы даже не заметил использование ресурсов не по назначению (иначе то уволим. нет)
:keyboard: Рабочий ноут, монитор и вашу любимую эргономичную клавиатуру, если такую соизволите
:notbad: Некислую зарплату

Свои вопросы и резюме кидайте мне!
Буду рад ответить:relieved:
<@U6MDMAG6T>
